  <Placemark>
   <name>Flood Advisory issued September 13 at 12:24PM CDT until September 13 at 3:00PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</name>
   <styleUrl>#sev_minor</styleUrl>
   <Style>
    <BalloonStyle />
   </Style>
   <Snippet>* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall continues.

* WHERE...Northeastern Burke county.

* WHEN...Until 300 PM CDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 1222 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to
thunderstorms. Minor flooding is ongoing or expected in the
advisory area. Between 2 and 4 inches of rain have fallen.
- Additional rainfall amounts up to 1 inch are expected over
the area. This additional rain will result in minor flooding.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Bowbells, Flaxton and Northgate.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood</Snippet>
