  <Placemark>
   <name>Flash Flood Warning issued September 13 at 10:39AM MDT until September 13 at 1:45PM MDT by NWS Salt Lake City UT</name>
   <styleUrl>#sev_severe</styleUrl>
   <Style>
    <BalloonStyle />
   </Style>
   <Snippet>FFWSLC

The National Weather Service in Salt Lake City has issued a

* Flash Flood Warning for...
East Central Emery County in central Utah...

* Until 145 PM MDT.

* At 1039 AM MDT, Doppler radar indicated thunderstorms producing
heavy rain across the warned area. Between 2.5 and 4 inches of
rain have fallen. Additional rainfall amounts of 1 to 2 inches are
possible in the headwaters of the Saleratus Wash. Flash flooding
is ongoing or expected to begin shortly.

HAZARD...Life threatening flash flooding. Thunderstorms
producing flash flooding.

SOURCE...Radar.

IMPACT...Life threatening flash flooding of creeks and streams,
urban areas, highways, streets and underpasses.

* Some locations that will experience flash flooding include...
Saleratus Wash near Green River.</Snippet>
